The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, February 07, 2004 				 Subsidy for Varishtha Bima raised
																								New Delhi, Feb. 6 (PTI): Enthused by the success of LICs Varishtha Pension Bima Yojana, the government has decided to increase the subsidy for the pension scheme for senior citizens to Rs 150 crore in the next fiscal.																								Initial budgetary subsidy to Life Insurance Corporation for the Varishtha scheme was Rs 30 crore. This was revised to Rs 45 crore this fiscal considering the overwhelming response, a finance ministry official said here today. 																								For 2004-05, the government had budgeted Rs 150 crore subsidy to LIC for its pension scheme, the official said.																								Confirming the move, LIC chairman S. B. Mathur said the corporation hopes to mop up Rs 5,500-6,000 crore from the Varishtha scheme this fiscal. 
